definitions.definition: A Japanese dish made of small portions of sticky white rice flavored with vinegar, usually wrapped in seaweed and filled or topped with fish, vegetables or meat.
examples: For the vegetarians, she served cucumber sushi .
He went to a Japanese restaurant and ordered sushi and noodles.

definitions.definition: One of the portions from this dish.
Raw fish, especially as a Japanese dish.
